{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"548","heading":"Advisory Committee on United States Outlying Areas and Freely Associated States","label":"548 Advisory Committee on United States Outlying Areas and Freely Associated States","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptI/ch5/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Deadlines for Establishment, Initial Appointments, and Initial Meeting–(d), , , provided that:Pub. L. 117–263, div. E, title LI, § 5102(b)136 Stat. 3208Dec. 23, 2022“(b).—Deadline for EstablishmentNot later than 180 days after the date of the enactment of this Act [], the Secretary of Veterans Affairs shall establish the advisory committee required by , United States Code, as added by subsection (a) of this section.Dec. 23, 2022section 548 of title 38“(c).—Deadline for Initial AppointmentsNot later than 90 days after the date on which the Secretary establishes the advisory committee required by such section 548, the members of such advisory committee shall be appointed.“(d).—Initial MeetingNot later than 180 days after the date on which the Secretary establishes the advisory committee required by such section 548, such advisory committee shall hold its first meeting.”"],"amendments":["Deadlines for Establishment, Initial Appointments, and Initial Meeting–(d), , , provided that:Pub. L. 117–263, div. E, title LI, § 5102(b)136 Stat. 3208Dec. 23, 2022“(b).—Deadline for EstablishmentNot later than 180 days after the date of the enactment of this Act [], the Secretary of Veterans Affairs shall establish the advisory committee required by , United States Code, as added by subsection (a) of this section.Dec. 23, 2022section 548 of title 38“(c).—Deadline for Initial AppointmentsNot later than 90 days after the date on which the Secretary establishes the advisory committee required by such section 548, the members of such advisory committee shall be appointed.“(d).—Initial MeetingNot later than 180 days after the date on which the Secretary establishes the advisory committee required by such section 548, such advisory committee shall hold its first meeting.”"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Establishment","label":"a .—Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall establish an advisory committee, to be known as the “Advisory Committee on United States Outlying Areas and Freely Associated States”, to provide advice and guidance to the Secretary on matters relating to covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Duties","label":"b .—Duties","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To advise the Secretary on matters relating to covered veterans, including how the Secretary may improve the programs and services of the Department to better serve such veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To identify for the Secretary evolving issues of relevance to covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To propose clarifications, recommendations, and solutions to address issues raised by covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To provide a forum for covered veterans, veterans service organizations serving covered veterans, and the Department to discuss issues and proposals for changes to regulations, policies, and procedures of the Department.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To identify priorities for and provide advice to the Secretary on appropriate strategies for consultation with veterans service organizations serving covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To encourage the Secretary to work with the heads of other Federal departments and agencies, and Congress, to ensure covered veterans are provided the full benefits of their status as covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To highlight contributions of covered veterans in the Armed Forces.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fb%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To conduct other duties as determined appropriate by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Membership","label":"c .—Membership","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Committee shall be comprised of 15 voting members appointed by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"American Samoa.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Guam.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Puerto Rico.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Virgin Islands of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vi","heading":null,"label":"vi","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/vi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fvi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Federated States of Micronesia.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vii","heading":null,"label":"vii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/vii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fvii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Republic of the Marshall Islands.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"viii","heading":null,"label":"viii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A/viii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FA%2Fviii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Republic of Palau.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not fewer than half of the members appointed are covered veterans, unless the Secretary determines that an insufficient number of qualified covered veterans are available.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Each member appointed resides in an area specified in subparagraph (A).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In appointing members pursuant to paragraph (1), the Secretary may consult with any Member of Congress who represents an area specified in paragraph (2)(A).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In addition to the members appointed pursuant to paragraph (1), the Committee shall be comprised of such ex officio members as the Secretary of State and the Secretary of the Interior shall appoint from among employees of the Department of State and the Department of the Interior, respectively.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Terms; Vacancies","label":"d .—Terms; Vacancies","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall be appointed for a term of two years; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fd%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may be reappointed to serve an additional two-year term.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 180 days after the Secretary (or in the case of an ex officio member, the Secretary of State or the Secretary of the Interior, as the case may be) receives notice of a vacancy in the Committee, the vacancy shall be filled in the same manner as the original appointment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Meeting Format and Frequency","label":"e .—Meeting Format and Frequency","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), the Committee shall meet in-person with the Secretary not less frequently than once each year and hold monthly conference calls as necessary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Department protocols; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"timing and budget considerations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":".—Additional Representation","label":"f .—Additional Representation","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Representatives of relevant Federal departments and agencies may attend meetings of the Committee and provide information to the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"One representative of the Department shall attend each meeting of the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Ff%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Ff%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may not be considered voting members of the Committee; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/f/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Ff%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may not receive additional compensation for services performed with respect to the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":".—Subcommittees","label":"g .—Subcommittees","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fg%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Committee may establish subcommittees.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may, in consultation with the Committee, appoint a member to a subcommittee established under paragraph (1) who is not a member of the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fg%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A subcommittee established under paragraph (1) may enhance the function of the Committee, but may not supersede the authority of the Committee or provide direct advice or work products to the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":".—Reports","label":"h .—Reports","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"containing such recommendations as the Committee may have for legislative or administrative action; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"describing the activities of the Committee during the previous two years.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"giving the Committee an opportunity to review such written response; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"including in such written response any comments the Committee considers appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"each report the Secretary receives under paragraph (1); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/h/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fh%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"each written response the Secretary submits under paragraph (2).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"i","heading":".—Committee Personnel Matters","label":"i .—Committee Personnel Matters","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A member of the Committee shall be allowed travel expenses, including per diem in lieu of subsistence, at rates authorized for an employee of an agency under subchapter I of chapter 57 of title 5 while away from the home or regular place of business of the member in the performance of the duties of the Committee.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"j","heading":".—Consultation","label":"j .—Consultation","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/j","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fj","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In carrying out this section, the Secretary shall consult with veterans service organizations serving covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"k","heading":".—Termination","label":"k .—Termination","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/k","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fk","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Committee shall terminate on the date that is 10 years after the date of the enactment of this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"l","heading":".—Definitions","label":"l .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Veterans’ Affairs of the House of Representatives; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Veterans’ Affairs of the Senate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Committee” means the Advisory Committee on United States Outlying Areas and Freely Associated States established under subsection (a).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “covered veteran” means a veteran residing in an area specified in subsection (c)(2)(A).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"serves the interests of covered veterans;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has covered veterans in substantive and policymaking positions within the organization; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s548/l/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs548%2Fl%2F4%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has demonstrated experience working with covered veterans.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
